reviews.text: Our indigenous people cannot afford to be greedy. We give you the money you ask for, but you don't give the thing the customer wants. We ordered  butter chicken Some of it is black, some is white, some is fresh, some is stale. This is not a good thing, right? The spices make it dark, but the quality is good. You want what you ask for, we give you the money. Why don't you give the thing that is good? You should give it.

Third time coming here for dinner. We drive about 30 min from Davis county to eat here. The first two times were excellent. This time the service fell short. The same two gals were serving, but this time they were inattentive and completely forgot our appetizer. We ordered Samosa that never came. The restaurant wasn't busy and it was a Saturday evening. Our water wasn't refilled the whole time and after swiping my card one of the girls literally threw our check on the table! We were shocked, because the first two visits were during busier times and the service was better.

The food was good, and made with the requested dietary restriction modifications. All three times the food was good, which is why we kept coming back.

But, after the way we were treated this time, we will give other restaurants a chance.

India House is the Indian gem of its area. It‚Äôs a very small business, with a cozy, quiet atmosphere. The staff is so sweet and friendly, and it‚Äôs nice to see the same faces every time we go.

My favorite dish is the Chicken Coconut Korma! We pick up our food half the time because it lasts and reheats so well.
We‚Äôve been coming here for years, it‚Äôs my go-to for Indian food! I‚Äôm never disappointed

My family and I absolutely love India House! We eat here all the time it's our favorite Indian restaurant in salt lake. The family who owns and runs this restaurant are simply amazing. Due to frequenting this lovely restaurant on a regular basis we have become regulars and they are willing to go above and beyond for their customers. This year for my husband birthday they accommodated us by making his favorite appetizer that is no longer on the menu. Everything, as usual, tasted wonderful!
